<br>
It's amazing how much nuclear power has been used in fiction. Many early script writers realised it was the only available technology remotely able to fuel their concepts.<br>
<br>
Back in the 60's such wild idea's seemed semi-plausible and although Batman was a comedy series one has to wonder what might have been. Noone realised the fearmongers would take over fiction writing. The primary source of information for the masses. Then portray nuclear power as evil. <br>
<br>
Nuclear power could have been embraced instead of shunned and there is no telling how advanced it might be today. New ways of tapping into the enormous energies of Uranium would doubtless have been discovered and known methods improved upon. Just as the steam engine led to the petrol driven combustion engine. Nuclear power remains at the steam engine stage because of ecowackies killing of interest in this exciting new science. If only we had followed the dream we might actually have, dare I suggest it, a real atomic car. Nuclear submarines were once science fiction.  <br>
