Ford Nucleon <br>
In 1958, during an age when technological optimism far outstripped practical and environmental concerns, Ford announced plans to build a nuclear-powered automobile named the Nucleon. The design called for a small nuclear reactor to be mounted on the trunk lid. The car's power was adjusted by connecting the accelerator pedal with the fuel rods! The car was never built, but prototypes of the body were displayed at auto shows around the country. An accident in one of these cars would have made the famous exploding Pinto gas tank problem seem relatively minor.<br>
- Michael Natkin<br>
